The paper discusses the modeling of bibliographic data and its suitability for the Semantic Web, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the organization and retrieval of bibliographic data. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) and cs.DB (Databases) are also likely categories as they deal with the management and organization of data. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possible category as the paper discusses the establishment of a network of correlations between entities and names. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category but still relevant as the paper discusses the socio-cultural meanings and interpretations of names.
